    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="539"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112A European War 1939/31033:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-22">May 22,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received May 22—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>959. For Foreign Funds Control Division. The interim Foreign Minister<note n="42"
                        xml:id="d539fn42">Pedro Zilveti Arce.</note> in an interview published in
                        <hi rend="italic">Ultima Hora</hi> May 21 is quoted as having said: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Faithful to its tradition of respect for formal agreements the National
                            Government will carry out scrupulously its international promises.
                            Concretely insofar as this may refer to the practical application of the
                            recommendations adopted by the Inter-American Conference on Systems of
                            Economic and Financial Control which we signed in Washington in July of
                            last year the Government is studying carefully their application. We
                            will very shortly take the first step to make effective that control in
                            accordance with the constitution the laws and the special regulations
                            under which foreign industry and commerce are carried on within the
                            country. There is then no reason for lack of confidence nor for
                            impatience. The executive will submit at the proper <pb facs="0609"
                                n="597" xml:id="pg_597"/> time to the legislature other analogous
                            measures designed to fulfill its obligations under those
                            recommendations.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
